WorkItem.Description:
Using Rawr 2.0.2 and Character profiler Version: 3.0.0 (Author: calvin  X-Date: October 08, 2008), I get:
 
Error reading saved variable file: The given key was not present in the dictionary
 
This happens as soon as I select the character profiler data file, before the character selection screen comes up.
 
Any suggestions how to id what is causing this?  Any debug flags I can toggle?
 
Thanks,
 
Keith
WorkItem.Summary: [LoadCharacter] Load From CharacterProfiler gives given key was not present in the dictionary

Comments.Message:
It was a corrupt character profiler file; deleting and recreating fixed the issue. Perhaps CP doesn't like two simultaneous wow instances running...but that's not an issue for here; please close this ticket.

Keith
